## Missing Clauses — Recommended Additions

{% set missing = clauses | selectattr("standard_flag", "equalto", "missing") | list %}
{% if missing %}
The following clauses are absent from the contract.  For each, consider whether
they are required for this agreement type and negotiating position.

{% for clause in missing %}
### {{ clause.clause_type | replace("-", " ") | title }}

{% if clause.clause_type == "limitation-of-liability" %}
**Why it matters**: Without this clause, liability defaults to unlimited.
Typical position: cap at 12 months of fees paid under the agreement.

{% elif clause.clause_type == "data-protection" %}
**Why it matters**: Required if personal data is processed under this agreement
(GDPR Art. 28 mandates a Data Processing Agreement).

{% elif clause.clause_type == "ip-ownership" %}
**Why it matters**: Without explicit assignment, IP created under an SOW may
default to the contractor/vendor under applicable IP law.

{% elif clause.clause_type == "indemnification" %}
**Why it matters**: Absent indemnification terms mean each party bears its own
losses; the counter-party may later seek indemnification via their standard terms.

{% elif clause.clause_type == "governing-law" %}
**Why it matters**: Without a governing law clause, courts may apply the law
of the counter-party's jurisdiction.

{% elif clause.clause_type == "termination" %}
**Why it matters**: Without termination provisions, exit rights may be
governed solely by statute (often requiring lengthy notice periods).

{% elif clause.clause_type == "force-majeure" %}
**Why it matters**: Without this, obligations remain in force during
extraordinary events (pandemics, natural disasters, war).

{% else %}
**Why it matters**: Review against your standard {{ contract.contract_type | upper }} template.
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
